musb: host - suniv DMA fixes to musb_host_rx/urb-cleanup (PIO fallback + flush)

Two host-path fixes needed by the sunxi_dma backend, which (unlike inventra/ux500)
gates short/misaligned transfers to PIO and shares one FIFO datapath between PIO
and DMA via a global VEND0 BUS_SEL bit:

1) musb_host_rx(): when musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41() declines the RX DMA
   (channel_program returns 0 for a short transfer) the helper released
   hw_ep->rx_channel, but the caller's local `dma` still pointed at it, so the
   `if (!dma)` PIO block was skipped and the packet was dropped -> the AA session
   stalled after "Accessory linked". Refresh the local `dma` (now NULL) so RX
   falls through to PIO, mirroring the TX fallback.

2) musb_cleanup_urb(): on usb_kill_urb of a TX urb, musb_h_tx_flush_fifo() runs
   under musb->lock (IRQs off) and, when it cannot drain the FIFO, spins up to 1s
   (1000 x mdelay(1)) before dev_WARN_ONCE. On this 1663-class IC the CPU cannot
   touch the FIFO while the shared dedicated-DMA datapath is busy, so when the RX
   *video* DMA owns BUS_SEL a PIO TX cancel can never flush -> a 1s IRQs-off stall
   that starves the realtime AA read thread. Do NOT force the datapath back to PIO
   in that case: clearing BUS_SEL / aborting the RX channel corrupts the in-flight
   video (ep2 RX three-strikes -> disconnect -> re-enumeration storm). Instead
   flush normally when this TX ep owned DMA (already aborted above) or the datapath
   is idle, and skip the flush -- leaving the stale FIFO to be discarded on the next
   ep program, the app re-sends the OUT xfer -- when the RX DMA owns BUS_SEL. Gated
   on CONFIG_USB_SUNXI_DMA so only suniv builds touch reg 0x43.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_host.c
@@ -1924,8 +1924,14 @@
 			if (musb_rx_dma_in_inventra_cppi41(c, hw_ep, qh, urb,
 							   xfer_len, iso_err))
 				goto finish;
-			else
-				dev_err(musb->controller, "error: rx_dma failed\n");
+			/*
+			 * The DMA backend declined this RX (e.g. a short
+			 * transfer the sunxi engine rejects): the helper has
+			 * already released rx_channel, so drop our stale local
+			 * ref and fall through to the PIO path below instead of
+			 * losing the packet.  Mirrors the TX PIO fallback.
+			 */
+			dma = hw_ep->rx_channel;
 		}
 
 		if (!dma) {
@@ -2339,7 +2345,46 @@
 		if (is_dma_capable() && dma)
 			musb_platform_clear_ep_rxintr(musb, ep->epnum);
 	} else if (ep->epnum) {
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_USB_SUNXI_DMA)
+		/*
+		 * suniv MUSB shares ONE FIFO datapath and one dedicated-DMA
+		 * channel between the TX and RX directions, gated by the global
+		 * VEND0 BUS_SEL bit (reg 0x43). The CPU cannot touch the FIFO
+		 * while DMA owns the datapath, so on a TX-urb cancel FLUSHFIFO
+		 * may never clear FIFONOTEMPTY and musb_h_tx_flush_fifo() then
+		 * spins up to 1s with IRQs off (starving the realtime AA thread)
+		 * before it dev_WARN_ONCEs "Could not flush host TX fifo".
+		 *
+		 * Three cases:
+		 *  - This TX ep itself drove DMA (`dma` set above, already
+		 *    aborted): it owned the datapath, so return VEND0 to PIO and
+		 *    the flush is safe.
+		 *  - The datapath is idle (BUS_SEL clear): a normal PIO flush is
+		 *    safe.
+		 *  - Otherwise the RX *video* DMA is mid-flight and owns BUS_SEL
+		 *    while this is a small PIO control/bulk-OUT write. We must
+		 *    NOT clear BUS_SEL or abort the RX channel -- that corrupts
+		 *    the in-flight video (ep2 RX three-strikes -> disconnect ->
+		 *    re-enumeration storm). Skip the flush: the stale TX FIFO is
+		 *    discarded when the endpoint is next programmed and the app
+		 *    re-sends the cancelled OUT transfer.
+		 */
+		if (is_dma_capable() && dma) {
+			writeb(0, musb->mregs + 0x43);
+			csr = musb_readw(epio, MUSB_TXCSR);
+			csr &= ~(MUSB_TXCSR_DMAENAB | MUSB_TXCSR_DMAMODE);
+			musb_writew(epio, MUSB_TXCSR, csr);
+			musb_h_tx_flush_fifo(ep);
+		} else if (!(readb(musb->mregs + 0x43) & 1)) {
+			musb_h_tx_flush_fifo(ep);
+		} else {
+			dev_dbg(musb->controller,
+				"ep%d TX cancel while RX DMA owns BUS_SEL: skip flush\n",
+				ep->epnum);
+		}
+#else
 		musb_h_tx_flush_fifo(ep);
+#endif
 		csr = musb_readw(epio, MUSB_TXCSR);
 		csr &= ~(MUSB_TXCSR_AUTOSET
 			| MUSB_TXCSR_DMAENAB
